    "stem": "It is July. The treasurer of a regional telephone company expects to have $1 million cash on hand in about six weeks and intends to buy 90-day T-bills with the funds when they arrive. Cash bills are now selling at 94.42. The treasurer, fearing a fall in interest rates in the interim, hedges by buying one contract of September T-bill futures at 94.64. Contract size is $1 million. Six weeks later the treasurer buys 90-day bills in the cash market for 95.02 and offsets the long futures position at 95.14. Ignoring transaction costs, what is the effective price for the cash T-bills?",
